[49m[38;5;9m- 394     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Step 4: Aggregate evidence across all notes for each patient.** A single note rarely provides enough evidence to classify a patient. This step pulls together all the evidence accumulated across the patient's entire note corpus and organizes it by criterion. For criterion C2 (treatment failures), it counts distinct medications with failure assertions. For criterion C1 (MDD diagnosis), it counts the number of positive mentions across different encounters. The aggregation logic is criterion-specific because different criteria have different evidence thresholds.
